## Electron verify

| Tool | Role | Notes |
|------|------|-------|
| **electron-oracle** | Phase 1 smoke + optional Phase 2 CDP screenshot / DOM marker | `.cursor-plugin/agents/electron-oracle.md` + `.cursor/skills/electron-oracle/` |
| **control-ui** | CDP attach, Playwright `connectOverCDP`, screenshot loop | cursor-team-kit skill — load for Phase 2 |

**Visual verify loop:** dispatch `electron-oracle` after Electron UI or shell changes. Phase 1: `npm run smoke` (or documented smoke) with `ELECTRON_RUN_AS_NODE` cleared. Phase 2: launch with `--remote-debugging-port`, find app root marker (e.g. `[data-oracle-root]`), screenshot under `/tmp/electron-oracle-*.png`. **`npm run smoke` alone ≠ visual pass** — yields **VISUAL SKIP**, never VISUAL PASS.

**D-hybrid:** agent `readonly: true`; shell needs `required_permissions: ["all"]` for launch/CDP. If Task blocks shell/CDP → orchestrator runs Phase 1/2 inline (control-ui) and relays evidence — same escape hatch as ios-oracle enum unavailable.

**Tauri webviews** (`pi-harness-test`, `grok-build-harness/gui`, etc.): design quality via **`ui-design-quality`** (webview lane). **Never** dispatch `electron-oracle` for Tauri. Ship verify = labeled manual/build (repo tauri/npm smoke, screenshot) until a separate tauri-oracle exists. Rust/`src-tauri` is out of scope for design-quality work.

**Not ported from Claude Code:** `swift-lsp` and `apple-platform-build-tools` plugins — Cursor uses `code-worker` + local `xcodebuild` oracle instead.
